member.summary:
Creates and returns a named special ordered set (SOS) of type 2
from a number of elements, starting at the specified index,
of the array of variables and weights.

Returns slack values from the solution pool
for a range of num consecutive rows,
starting from the index specified by start, of an LP matrix.

remarks.p:
Cplex.ConflictPossibleMember the constraint
             not been proven not to participate in the conflict;
             that is, it might participate, it might not.

member.remarks:
 The following example shows how to test whether an aborter is
 currently in use; that is, how to test for an empty handle.

 
 if (cplex.GetAborter().GetImpl())
     System.Console.WriteLine("There is an aborter installed.");
 else
     System.Console.Writeline("No aborter installed.");


This method can be invoked only from Cplex.Callback.Context.Id.Relaxation;
             it will throw an exception when invoked from another context. 
            
             
             Throws ILOG.Concert.Exception if an error occurs.

remarks.p:
In other words, the cut is filtered through the CPLEX process;
it may not even be added to the relaxation;
